<section class="building" id="building">
  <div class="wrap">
    <p class="eyebrow">Possibilities</p>
    <h2 class="section-h" style="color:var(--cream);">What Could This Land Become?</h2>
    <p class="lead">
      A Community Land Trust takes land off the speculative market. The community owns the ground.
      What gets built on it is up to the people who live here. Here are some of the possibilities
      the coalition is exploring.
    </p>
    <div class="cards">
      <div class="card">
        <span class="icon">🌿</span>
        <h3>Community Land Trust</h3>
        <p>The land could be held in perpetuity for community benefit, never flipped or redeveloped away from a community-determined mission. This is the legal and moral core of the project.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <span class="icon">☀️</span>
        <h3>Year-Round Market Pavilion</h3>
        <p>Shade structures and landscape design could make the outdoor market functional in Portland's rain — turning a seasonal venue into a year-round community fixture.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <span class="icon">🏗️</span>
        <h3>Mass Timber Community Hub</h3>
        <p>A sustainably built structure could house a commissary kitchen, commercial cold storage, and deep freezers — infrastructure that local food makers and vendors could grow into.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <span class="icon">🌳</span>
        <h3>Protected Green Space</h3>
        <p>Green space for Montavilla — open, welcoming, and part of the neighborhood long-term.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <span class="icon">🏘️</span>
        <h3>Affordable Housing or Mixed Use</h3>
        <p>The site is zoned for up to four stories. A community-controlled mixed-use building — with permanently affordable housing, ground-floor space for local enterprise, or both — is one of the directions the neighborhood could choose.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p class="lead" style="margin-top:1.75rem; font-style:italic; color:rgba(122,158,126,0.85);">
      These are starting points, not final plans. The coalition will host listening sessions
      to hear what the neighborhood wants.
    </p>
    <div style="margin-top:2.5rem;">
      <a href="/Montavilla_Community_Land_Trust_Prospectus.pdf" target="_blank" class="btn btn-ghost">
        Read the Full Prospectus →
      </a>
      <p style="font-size:0.78rem; color:rgba(122,158,126,0.55); margin-top:0.6rem; font-style:italic;">
        The prospectus describes one possible scenario. The coalition is exploring multiple options.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
